Release Notes:

To some, Swedish music is defined by ABBA and other perfectly
glossy pop music confections; to others, it&#039;s defined by
the Hellacopters. Veterans of a slew of Swedish punk and metal
bands, the Hellacopters formed in the mid 1990s and have been
churning out textbook high-octane rock ever since.

Combining the best of Detroit proto-punk, a la the Stooges
and the MC5, with the scorching shriek of AC/DC and Van Halen,
the Hellacopters have no intentions of reinventing the wheel;
rather, their simple goal is to keep it rolling on, rolling
strong. Raise your devil horns...now.
